# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "A little later in the day, Sarah managed to find a chance to slip into Razaphel's room."
    new "A little later in the day, Sarah managed to find a chance to slip into Razaphel's room."

    old "The spirit was no longer bound to this place, but it was isolated enough for Sarah to meet the creature in private."
    new "The spirit was no longer bound to this place, but it was isolated enough for Sarah to meet the creature in private."

    old "Sarah let the name linger."
    new "Sarah let the name linger."

    old "Razaphel!"
    new "Razaphel!"

    old "Speaking its name more forcefully, Sarah hoped to draw the spirit out."
    new "Speaking its name more forcefully, Sarah hoped to draw the spirit out."

    old "He drew out her name as he spoke it."
    new "He drew out her name as he spoke it."

    old "I am glad we can meet so soon again."
    new "I am glad we can meet so soon again."

    old "I have questions for you."
    new "I have questions for you."

    old "She saw the spirit move about."
    new "She saw the spirit move about."

    old "Any matter in particular?"
    new "Any matter in particular?"

    old "You were here before me. Do you have any idea who Metis is?"
    new "You were here before me. Do you have any idea who Metis is?"

    old "A hissing sound emerged from the spirit."
    new "A hissing sound emerged from the spirit."

    old "The mage's previous pet."
    new "The mage's previous pet."

    old "Sarah ignored Razaphel indirectly referring to her as a pet."
    new "Sarah ignored Razaphel indirectly referring to her as a pet."

    old "Is there anything I should know about him?"
    new "Is there anything I should know about him?"

    old "He's here. In the house."
    new "He's here. In the house."

    old "The spirit's voice drifted, then went silent for a moment."
    new "The spirit's voice drifted, then went silent for a moment."

    old "Be careful around that one."
    new "Be careful around that one."

    old "Why? Is he dangerous?"
    new "Why? Is he dangerous?"

    old "Too clever for his own good. Ambitious to the point of sin. Always pretending."
    new "Too clever for his own good. Ambitious to the point of sin. Always pretending."

    old "Pretending?"
    new "Pretending?"

    old "Every smile. Every word. Every gesture."
    new "Every smile. Every word. Every gesture."

    old "It's all a performance to him. Nothing comes out of him that he has not carefully considered."
    new "It's all a performance to him. Nothing comes out of him that he has not carefully considered."

    old "He's that calculating?"
    new "He's that calculating?"

    old "I had my occasional encounter with him when he was still studying here."
    new "I had my occasional encounter with him when he was still studying here."

    old "Sarah wondered what that meant exactly."
    new "Sarah wondered what that meant exactly."

    old "He believed he could manipulate me. Draw out certain knowledges."
    new "He believed he could manipulate me. Draw out certain knowledges."

    old "Such as?"
    new "Such as?"

    old "Many. But above all, it was Daemonology that he favored."
    new "Many. But above all, it was Daemonology that he favored."

    old "Sarah could feel her attention perk up."
    new "Sarah could feel her attention perk up."

    old "Daemonology? He offered to teach me."
    new "Daemonology? He offered to teach me."

    old "What is it exactly?"
    new "What is it exactly?"

    old "Among the order, it is considered the most depraved of the Arts."
    new "Among the order, it is considered the most depraved of the Arts."

    old "It is the very Art that produced the welding of the worlds. The ritual that drew my world into yours."
    new "It is the very Art that produced the welding of the worlds. The ritual that drew my world into yours."

    old "You're saying...he can do that?"
    new "You're saying...he can do that?"

    old "The spirit moved about."
    new "The spirit moved about."

    old "Not quite. He is a skilled mage in his own right, but he does not even come close to the talent required for a spell like that."
    new "Not quite. He is a skilled mage in his own right, but he does not even come close to the talent required for a spell like that."

    old "His only advantage is that he runs ahead of everyone else. Blind to the risk."
    new "His only advantage is that he runs ahead of everyone else. Blind to the risk."

    old "Daemonology, as practiced by him, is little more than the art of cutting between the veils of different worlds."
    new "Daemonology, as practiced by him, is little more than the art of cutting between the veils of different worlds."

    old "To reach out and draw back creatures from beyond this dimension, and pull them into ours."
    new "To reach out and draw back creatures from beyond this dimension, and pull them into ours."

    old "Why do so few practice it?"
    new "Why do so few practice it?"

    old "Because their order was formed in the fall of the ancient empire. They fear it, the same way a man burned might fear the flame."
    new "Because their order was formed in the fall of the ancient empire. They fear it, the same way a man burned might fear the flame."

    old "But is it powerful?"
    new "But is it powerful?"

    old "Always so demanding."
    new "Always so demanding."

    old "It's an honest question."
    new "It's an honest question."

    old "Yes, it can be powerful, to a degree."
    new "Yes, it can be powerful, to a degree."

    old "Most creatures pulled into this world can't survive long, with rare exceptions."
    new "Most creatures pulled into this world can't survive long, with rare exceptions."

    old "Sarah looked around her."
    new "Sarah looked around her."

    old "Like this house."
    new "Like this house."

    old "But the Art is a madness. It is too chaotic to control. One risks just easily summoning a wicked creature."
    new "But the Art is a madness. It is too chaotic to control. One risks just easily summoning a wicked creature."

    old "And some mages, foolish in their ambition, have been known to be pulled in the other way."
    new "And some mages, foolish in their ambition, have been known to be pulled in the other way."

    old "The other way?"
    new "The other way?"

    old "Yes. A mage creates a link between oneself and a creature in a different world. Then they cut the veil and pull it through."
    new "Yes. A mage creates a link between oneself and a creature in a different world. Then they cut the veil and pull it through."

    old "Some of these creatures are little more than wild animals, too weak of mind to resist."
    new "Some of these creatures are little more than wild animals, too weak of mind to resist."

    old "Others are near your kind, intelligent, but unskilled in magic and lacking any defense."
    new "Others are near your kind, intelligent, but unskilled in magic and lacking any defense."

    old "Yet some..."
    new "Yet some..."

    old "Some are clever and can weave spells of their own."
    new "Some are clever and can weave spells of their own."

    old "Should you contact such a creature by accident, it might as easily pull you into its world, rather than the other way around."
    new "Should you contact such a creature by accident, it might as easily pull you into its world, rather than the other way around."

    old "Sarah felt a cold sensation coming over her."
    new "Sarah felt a cold sensation coming over her."

    old "What...what would such a world look like?"
    new "What...what would such a world look like?"

    old "I cannot begin to speak of it."
    new "I cannot begin to speak of it."

    old "The other worlds are not only different in shape, dimension or material."
    new "The other worlds are not only different in shape, dimension or material."

    old "They can even vary by the very laws that govern them."
    new "They can even vary by the very laws that govern them."

    old "You might appear in a world where time crawls, and you live out a million lifetimes at the hand of some demon."
    new "You might appear in a world where time crawls, and you live out a million lifetimes at the hand of some demon."

    old "So...you say I should avoid such knowledge."
    new "So...you say I should avoid such knowledge."

    old "The spirit moved closer to her, pressing its facemask close to her face."
    new "The spirit moved closer to her, pressing its facemask close to her face."

    old "No, Sarah."
    new "No, Sarah."

    old "I am not your old teacher, warning you to hide like a child from the truth of the world."
    new "I am not your old teacher, warning you to hide like a child from the truth of the world."

    old "I only offer you words of warning."
    new "I only offer you words of warning."

    old "Tread carefully, for you walk on dangerous ground."
    new "Tread carefully, for you walk on dangerous ground."

    old "With that, the spirit faded into nothingness."
    new "With that, the spirit faded into nothingness."

    old "Sarah remained behind in the room, alone."
    new "Sarah remained behind in the room, alone."

    old "She had far more questions, but those would have to wait for another time."
    new "She had far more questions, but those would have to wait for another time."

    old "Despite their pact, the spirit still seemed hesitant with her."
    new "Despite their pact, the spirit still seemed hesitant with her."

    old "Sarah sighed and turned to leave."
    new "Sarah sighed and turned to leave."

    old "Whatever it was, it would have to wait for another day."
    new "Whatever it was, it would have to wait for another day."

    old "The creature gave no response."
    new "The creature gave no response."

    old "She didn't know if the spirit was here and refused to answer, or if it was somewhere else."
    new "She didn't know if the spirit was here and refused to answer, or if it was somewhere else."

    old "Perhaps rejecting it had left its mark. Did it even have an ego to bruise? Sarah didn't know."
    new "Perhaps rejecting it had left its mark. Did it even have an ego to bruise? Sarah didn't know."

    old "It also didn't matter. The spirit was silent and would not speak to her."
    new "It also didn't matter. The spirit was silent and would not speak to her."

